The case against the men who are accused of raping a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga has been postponed to 18 January. CAPE TOWN - Eight young men accused of the rape of a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga will ring in the New Year behind bars.The accused, between the ages of 18 and 20, made a brief appearance in the Wynberg Magistrates Court on Tuesday.It's alleged they raped the teenage girl in two shacks in the area last month.The accused's relatives, who packed the public gallery, gasped and whispered angrily as they heard their children would be spending the festive season in a prison cell.The men stood quietly in the dock with sombre expressions.One of the accused is believed to have abducted the victim at gunpoint while she was walking along Robert Sobukwe Road.They're due back in the dock on 18 January.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)